**In a world destroyed by war and chaos, a group of survivors have taken refuge underground in a massive underground tunnels and chambers. The few remaining human survivals are ruled over by a small group of leaders underground who hold absolute power over their lives. This is the world that Jane has known for her entire life. Jane is the daughter of a scientist who has been given special access to the surface. As she grows up, Jane becomes increasingly curious about the world above, and she longs to experience it for herself. However, the leaders have strict rules in place that prevent anyone from leaving the underground world. Despite these rules, Jane begins to sneak out of the complex and explore the black market where she can find illegal goods like burgers and chocolate, which are banned in the underground world. But her curiosity does not stop there. She begins to ask questions and starts to uncover a shocking truth about the world she has grown up in. Through her interactions with a reporter, Jane learns that the leaders have been lying to the people of the underground for years. They have been telling them that the surface is uninhabitable and that all life on Earth has been destroyed. But Jane discovers that this is a lie, and that the world above is actually thriving. When the leaders find out that Jane has been asking questions, they send a group of soldiers to silence the reporter. The network cuts off, leaving Jane to struggle with the realization that everything she has been told is a lie. She decides to take matters into her own hands and make a daring escape to the surface. As she emerges into the light, Jane is shocked to find that the world is not a barren wasteland, as she had been led to believe.
